responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;
In morning's hush, I seek Thy tone;
No idol's echo stirs my soul—
But thirst for Thee, my only goal.

Deserts may stretch, their silence deep,
My spirit pants, my eyelids weep,
Yet in Thy shadow, shade is found;
My heart is whole on holy ground.

The world may scatter dust and bone,
But Thou, O Lord, art mine alone;
In every ache, in every song,
My longing lifts to Thee, lifelong.

Farewell, thou child of my right hand, and joy;
Soft echo of laughter now fading from halls.
Your absence, a silence that naught can alloy;
A shadow that deepens as twilight befalls.
Yet hope in its gentlest whisper reminds:
You dwell in the hush between heartbeats and sighs.
The warmth of your touch in my memory binds,
A promise of dawn in the night of goodbyes.
Go gentle, my dearest, to dreams far above;
Farewell, as I send you with infinite love.
